# Nombre del paquete (minúsculas-separado-con-guiones)
name: bardinux-default-settings

# Autor
author: Enrique Hernández Bello <quique@osl.ull.es>

# Priority
priority: optional

# Section
section: misc

# Descripción corta
shortdesc: "Default settings and artwork for the Bardinux desktop system (KDE Version)."

# Descipción larga, las lineas han de estar separadas por "\n "
longdesc: "This package contains the default settings and used by Bardinux. It also\n includes artwork and Bardinux branding."

# Versión del paquete
version: 1.0~dev16

# Cambios en esta versión
changes:
    - Runs update-grub after install forcing to apply grub configuration.
    - Changed the hook to load KDE profiles. Now supports multiple profiles.
    - Added a workaround for NetworkManager problems (LP: #553994)
    - Added configuration to get better flash performance.
